The paper deals with text retrieval systems and similarity search, which are core topics in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of vector spaces and clustering algorithms also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of dynamic weights and tradeoffs between query time and output quality points to a possible application of machine learning techniques (cs.AI).
